The Kogi State Police Command has confirmed that three people were killed in the attack launched by gunmen on Agbenema village in Omala local government area of the state. Locals have said that 10 people were killed during attacks carried out on Agbenema, Ayade, Ajichepa and Opada villages in Omala LGA of the state. A statement issued yesterday by the Public Relations Officer of the Kogi State Police Command, William Aya, confirmed the killing of three people at Agbenema and said personnel had since been deployed to the area to restore order. The PPRO said those deployed to the troubled community included men of the Police Mobile Force (PMF), Counter Terrorism Unit (CTU), Special Anti-Robbery Squad (SARS) as well as conventional police personnel.